IT Budget




The Federal Home Loan Bank of Des Moines is one of twelve Banks within the Federal Home Loan Bank system. This Bank primarily supports member institutions help promote economic development. They provide financial assistance to these members for home mortgages,… MoreThe Federal Home Loan Bank of Des Moines is one of twelve Banks within the Federal Home Loan Bank system. This Bank primarily supports member institutions help promote economic development. They provide financial assistance to these members for home mortgages, home equity loans, small business and rural loans, as well as agricultural loans.

FHLB merged with the Federal Home Loan Bank of Seattle in 2015.
The information technology department at the Federal Home Loan Bank of Des Moines (FHLB Des Moines) is a branch of the Federal Home Loan Banks. The IT department remains separate from those of the other twelve Banks of the Federal… MoreThe information technology department at the Federal Home Loan Bank of Des Moines (FHLB Des Moines) is a branch of the Federal Home Loan Banks. The IT department remains separate from those of the other twelve Banks of the Federal Home Loan Bank system.

The IT department is classified into two major groups. A director handles all operations pertaining to system maintenance, which includes infrastructure. Another director heads a group of staff members responsible for programming, which also includes applications development. The Bank's IT staff members specialize in several technologies including SQL, Microsoft and Oracle. 

For 2012, the IT Department has decided to implement business applications from Calypso to support front and back office services. In February of 2011, FHLB Des Moines decided to implement Response Analytics Mortgage Asset Management solution to support risk management. Additionally, the bank has undergone server virtualization using VMware.





